## Voxel addon for WP all import

### **Import data to Voxel**

**[Download WP all import plugin \[Free version\]](https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-all-import/)**

**[Download Voxel Add-on for WP All Import](docs.getvoxel.io_wp-content_uploads_2025_08_wpai-voxel-addon.zip_.md)**

This plugin should be installed in your Voxel activated website. Instructions below

## How to import data to Voxel

Install and activate **WP all import** and **Voxel addon for WP all import**

[![](data:image/png;base64,)](https://getvoxel.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/Plugins-%E2%80%B9-CityGuide-%E2%80%94-WordPress.png)

To start an import, go to **WP admin  All import  New import**

Press **Upload a file** and upload your CSV/XML file where your data is stored

[![](data:image/png;base64,)](https://getvoxel.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/New-Import-%E2%80%B9-CityGuide-%E2%80%94-WordPress.png)

Once the file is uploaded, select the post type in the dropdown and click continue until you arrive at step 3

[![](data:image/png;base64,)](https://getvoxel.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/New-Import-%E2%80%B9-CityGuide-%E2%80%94-WordPress-1.png)

Step three is where you will map data you need to import. On the right hand side, the sidebar will display all the individual columns found in the file you uploaded.

[![](data:image/png;base64,)](https://getvoxel.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/New-Import-%E2%80%B9-CityGuide-%E2%80%94-WordPress-2.png)

Lets start with title and description: Drag and drop the columns which contain title and description to the corresponding fields as seen below

![](data:image/gif;base64,)

Next, scroll down and click **Voxel addon** accordion.

Here, all the Voxel fields you have made available for a specific post type are displayed and you can choose to import data to each field individually

Additionally, under **Taxonomies, Categories, Tags** you can import taxonomy terms

Example video:

https://i.imgur.com/nVoRFrP.mp4

Once youre done with mapping, proceed to next step. Click **Auto detect** button to create a unique identifier

[![](data:image/png;base64,)](https://getvoxel.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/New-Import-%E2%80%B9-CityGuide-%E2%80%94-WordPress-4.png)

then continue and run import

[![](data:image/png;base64,)](https://getvoxel.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/New-Import-%E2%80%B9-CityGuide-%E2%80%94-WordPress-5.png)[![](data:image/png;base64,)](https://getvoxel.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/New-Import-%E2%80%B9-CityGuide-%E2%80%94-WordPress-6.png)

Once the import is done, go to **WP admin  Post types  Edit post type  Filtering  Indexing ** Click **Index all posts.**

You should now see your imported posts and listings in front-end. Happy importing!
